Q3(a) Define Constructor and Types with Example.
Constructor: Special method to initialize objects. Same name as class, no return type.
Types: Default, Parameterized, Copy Constructor.
Example:
class Box {
 int w,h;
 Box(){ w=10; h=5; }
 Box(int x,int y){ w=x; h=y; }
 Box(Box b){ w=b.w; h=b.h; }
}
Q3(b) OR - Compare String, StringBuffer, and StringBuilder.
String - Immutable, Thread Safe.
StringBuffer - Mutable, Thread Safe.
StringBuilder - Mutable, Not Thread Safe.
Example:
String s="Hello"; StringBuffer sb=new StringBuffer("Hello");
StringBuilder sbd=new StringBuilder("Hello");
s=s+" Java"; sb.append(" Java"); sbd.append(" Java");
