Q4(a) What is Polymorphism? Explain Types.
Polymorphism: One interface, multiple implementations.
Types:
1. Compile-time (Overloading)
2. Run-time (Overriding)
Example:
class Display{ void show(int a){System.out.println(a);} void show(String s){System.out.println(s);} }
class Animal{ void sound(){System.out.println("Sound");} }
class Dog extends Animal{ void sound(){System.out.println("Bark");} }
Q4(b) OR - Method Overriding Rules.
Same method name & params, cannot reduce access, cannot override static/final/private.
Example:
class Parent{ void msg(){System.out.println("Parent");} }
class Child extends Parent{ void msg(){System.out.println("Child");} }

