Q6(b) OR - Explain AWT and its Role.
AWT (Abstract Window Toolkit) provides GUI components like Button, Frame, Label.
Example:
import java.awt.*;
class DemoAWT{
 DemoAWT(){
  Frame f=new Frame("Demo");
  Button b=new Button("Click");
  b.setBounds(100,100,80,30);
  f.add(b); f.setSize(300,300); f.setLayout(null); f.setVisible(true);
 }
 public static void main(String[] a){ new DemoAWT(); }
}
